snippet.textDisplay: I have noticed that more and more old artists are working to the end these days, they're not laying back on royalties after a one-hit-wonder anymore. They are giving everything they can to us for as long as they can. They have learned the true meaning of entertainment - it is not money or fame. It is being the soundtrack to people's lives, being someone who's there when nobody else is, someone who can be there even when you want to be alone, someone who cares about each and every person who hears their music.
